Notes: 'row_id' is an internal CSV identifier without semantic meaning in the ontology; it is best not mapped to any property and considered as a local identifier for data management only.
The 'patient_id' corresponds to identifying the patient related to the ProblemCondition; path #1 directly relates ProblemCondition to Patient, making it semantically most appropriate.

'diagnosis_code' is a code representing the condition, best mapped to the hasCode property of ProblemCondition. Although path #6 also points to Terminology via hasCode, the code literal is primary, so path #5 is more direct and appropriate.

The 'created_at' timestamp represents when the record was created. Path #17 (hasRecordDateTime) is most semantically appropriate to represent the record creation date/time associated with ProblemCondition.

'org_code' identifies an organization; path #8 links ProblemCondition to DataProviderInstitute, which represents the institute providing data, making it the best fit. No deeper paths for organization code exist, so 1-hop is optimal.

'org_name' is the name of the organization, which is an attribute of DataProviderInstitute (path #8). Although no explicit property for name is given, org_name logically belongs to the DataProviderInstitute entity reached by hasDataProviderInstitute.
